The paper discusses the use of a non-parametric independence measure as a loss-function for learning robust regression and classification models. This is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning, specifically in the areas of learning theory and statistical learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the adaptation of the loss-function to the task of unsupervised covariate shift, which involves learning on a source domain without access to any instances or labels from the unknown target domain. This task is relevant to several sub-categories, including cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.ST (Statistics), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
